-- South African Coal Prices Fall to Lowest Level in Three Months
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-03-12T12:38:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-12/south-african-coal-prices-fall-to-lowest-level-in-three-months.html
Coal export prices at  South
Africa ’s  Richards Bay , the continent’s biggest terminal for
shipping the fuel, fell to their lowest level in three months.  Prices  (CLSPSARB) declined 50 cents, or 0.5 percent, to $103.85 a
metric ton in the week ended March 9, the least since Dec. 16,
according to IHS McCloskey data on Bloomberg.  The price is quoted on a free-on-board basis, which
excludes delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw at 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
